Bottom line

The two R1 blocking findings are fixed correctly for the repository's supported gold-standard shapes, the new regression tests cover the intended failure modes, and I did not find a new blocking regression in `83f1161`. The only remaining note is that the parity claim in `_extract_first_reference_scalar()` is narrower than the docstring suggests because comparator-side guards for non-numeric / non-dict `reference_values` entries still do not exist.
